Defendant Michael L Edwards in court with attorney Daniel Mcmurray.  Brian J. Juech appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to count #1.  Court finds the defendant guilty of count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed and read in.  State makes recommendations.  Attorney Mcmurray makes statements.  Defendant makes statements. 
The Court Orders the Following: Count #1
Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:
90 Days Huber with STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  (Credit - 3 days).  
Term of Probation: 1 Year
Conditions of Probation:
Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
No Use or Possession of illegal controlled substances;
Inform agent of all prescriptions;
Sign all Releases for Agent;
Condition Time: 10 days Huber with  NON WORKING HOURS WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS - STAYED to be used at the Agents discretion
COSTS:  $243.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Surcharge: $200.00 to be paid as a condition of probation
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
